organic_results.title: College Students' Value Patterns in the 1950's and 1960's
organic_results.snippet: Surveys of men undergraduates in 1952 were replicated at Dartmouth in 1968 and at the University of Michigan in 1969 in an attempt to measure value changes and assess explanations for them. Commitments to political participation are stronger and privatism is weaker than in 1952. Otherdirectedness and embeddedness in groups have diminished, and the students' criticism of social institutions has intensified.
